article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- — Joe Pridgen's 23 points helped Montana defeat Denver 83-73 on Sunday night at the Stew Morrill Classic. Pridgen also contributed seven rebounds for the Grizzlies (3-3). Money Williams shot 5 of 9 from the field, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 7 from the line to add 17 points. Austin Patterson went 6 of 8 from the field (3 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 16 points. Sebastian Akins led the way for the Pioneers (3-3) with 21 points. Nicholas Shogbonyo added 16 points for Denver. Isaiah Addo-Ankrah had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
